The paper deals with machine learning techniques for predicting student dropout in MOOCs. The use of branch and bound algorithm for representation learning and the focus on interpretability suggest that the paper belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). However, the paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for analyzing clickstream data, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) or information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper deals with educational technology and pedagogy, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of computer education (cs.CE). Finally, the paper deals with the application of AI techniques to a specific domain, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
